54.5	Hydroxyl	Hydroxyl	A hydroxyl is a chemical functional group containing an oxygen atom connected by a covalent bond to a hydrogen atom, a pairing that can be simply understood as a substructure of the water molecule. When it appears, it imparts to chemical structures some of the reactive and interactive properties of the -OH of water is called the hydroxide anion; it bears a single negative charge largely residing on the more electronegative oxygen.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Hydroxyl3D.png/200px-Hydroxyl3D.png
